HEADWORD: Hydrostat
<hw>Hy"dro*stat</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
contrivance or apparatus to prevent the explosion of steam
boilers.</def></p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A device, usually electrical, for indicating or
regulating the height of water in a reservoir or receptacle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hydrostatical</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Hydrostatic</ent>⟦br⟧
